>
	<p class="lead-italic">
		Commonwealth Audiology provides repair and maintenance services for Unitron
		hearing aids in Georgetown, KY.
	</p>
	<p>
		At Commonwealth Audiology, we know how important it is to feel confident in
		the technology you rely on every day. While our clinic does not typically
		dispense Unitron hearing aids, we are pleased to offer professional
		cleaning, repair, troubleshooting, and maintenance for many current and
		legacy Unitron devices.
	</p>
	<p>
		We want your hearing to remain clear and consistent. If your Unitron
		devices need cleaning, troubleshooting, or repair, our audiologist is ready
		to provide the compassionate, detail-oriented care you deserve.
	</p>

	<TableOfContents />

	<h2>Understanding Unitron Hearing Technology</h2>
	<p>
		Unitron hearing aids are known for comfort, modern design, and sound
		processing that adapts to real-world listening. Their technology is built
		to help users follow conversations more easily, especially in busy or
		unpredictable environments.
	</p>
	<p>
		Below is an overview of current Unitron products. If you own one of these
		devices and need support, our team is here to help keep them performing
		their best.
	</p>

	<h2>Unitron Hearing Aid Models We Support</h2>

	<h3>Unitron Moxi S-R</h3>
	<p>
		Powered by Unitron's Smile platform, the Moxi S-R is a small, rechargeable
		device designed for flexible everyday listening.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Water-resistant build</li>
		<li>ChargerGo portable charging</li>
		<li>All-day battery life</li>
		<li>Bluetooth® streaming and app control</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Unitron Ativo</h3>
	<p>
		A value-friendly option offering comfort and clear, reliable sound for
		everyday communication.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Bluetooth streaming</li>
		<li>Hands-free calling</li>
		<li>Balanced sound across environments</li>
		<li>Lightweight, modern design</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Unitron Moxi V-RS</h3>
	<p>
		A discreet receiver-in-canal (RIC) model that automatically adapts as your
		surroundings change.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Made-For-All Bluetooth connectivity</li>
		<li>Remote Plus app control and Remote Care</li>
		<li>Rechargeable design</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Unitron Moxi Vivante (V)</h3>
	<p>
		Built for those who need strong performance in noisy places, the Vivante
		platform enhances speech from all directions.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Hands-free streaming</li>
		<li>Remote Plus app &amp; Remote Care</li>
		<li>Built-in tinnitus relief</li>
		<li>Suitable for mild to profound loss</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Unitron Stride Blu (B)</h3>
	<p>
		A behind-the-ear solution designed for durability, comfort, and strong
		amplification.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Hands-free Bluetooth streaming</li>
		<li>Remote Plus &amp; Remote Care</li>
		<li>Tinnitus support options</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Unitron Stride Blu (B) UP</h3>
	<p>
		Made for severe to profound hearing loss, offering strong amplification and
		automatic adjustments.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Bluetooth streaming</li>
		<li>Remote Plus app</li>
		<li>Tinnitus relief features</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Unitron Insera Blu (B)</h3>
	<p>Custom-fit devices built for comfort and all-day wear.</p>
	<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Optional Bluetooth streaming (model-dependent)</li>
		<li>Remote Plus app &amp; Remote Care</li>
		<li>Tinnitus relief noise generator</li>
	</ul>
	<p class="note-italic">
		Note: CIC and IIC styles do not support Bluetooth streaming due to size.
	</p>

