	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="What is the Unitron Smile platform?">
			<p>
				Smile is Unitron's most recent AI-driven processing system. It adjusts
				automatically to different listening environments so users hear more
				naturally with fewer manual adjustments.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="What technology levels does Unitron offer?">
			<p>
				Unitron typically uses four tiers: 3 (Essential), 5 (Standard), 7
				(Advanced), and 9 (Premium). Higher levels include more robust features
				for noisy environments and speech clarity.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="How long does it take to charge Unitron rechargeable hearing aids?">
			<p>
				Most models require about 3 hours for a full charge. A shorter charge
				(10–60 minutes) usually provides several hours of use.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

	<h2>Unitron Hearing Aid Support at Commonwealth Audiology</h2>
	<p>
		Although Commonwealth Audiology does not typically fit or dispense Unitron
		hearing aids, we are proud to serve patients who rely on these devices. Our
		audiologist can assist with:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Routine cleaning and maintenance</li>
		<li>Troubleshooting and device checks</li>
		<li>Dome, filter, and receiver replacements (when compatible)</li>
		<li>Programming adjustments (model-dependent)</li>
		<li>Guidance on when it may be time to upgrade</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		Our commitment is to help you hear your best, no matter which manufacturer
		you choose. If your Unitron devices need care, we're here to help.
	</p>
	<p>
		<a href="/contact/">Contact Commonwealth Audiology</a> today to schedule an appointment. We'll make
		sure your Unitron devices continue to support you with the clarity,
		comfort, and confidence you deserve.
	</p>
</InternalPage>
